        "timestamp": "2018-04-06 01:28:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nPlease see the <imageTags> section for Spotify plugin use.  It is already tagging the images following CIMAN 132:\n<imageTags>\n    <imageTag>${project.version}-SNAPSHOT-${maven.build.timestamp}Z</imageTag>\n    <imageTag>${project.version}</imageTag>\n    <imageTag>latest</imageTag>\n</imageTags>",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "0c951eb86b914a8aad7daa0b7c7b3adfc4a91782",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 51,
          "name": "Lusheng Ji",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "lji@research.att.com",
          "username": "wrider"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-04-06 01:31:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nMore over, CIMAN 132 does not show tags with letter 'v' in front.  My understanding is that 'v' is only used for release tags.  Is this correct?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "5e81edfd66f833eb28bbc1ac56130d173aa0baa1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-04-06 01:45:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYes, we were using \"v\" for releases.. but after this discussion happened we decided to go for the following tags:\n$VERSION-SNAPSHOT-YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ (for dev images)  \n$VERSION-STAGING-YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ (for staging images)\n$VERSION (for releases)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
